01-01-1900
CIVIL WAR!
Further Southern States Secede!
Confederate Armies on the Move!
Europeans Reluctant to Take Sides.
New Campaign Objectives!
The Demon of War has Awoken!
18
\tCivil War has erupted between the Union and Confederacy! Both nations are mustering volunteers to fill the ranks in their armies. Politicians are certain that the war will end in a neat showdown soon.\n\t Northern policy making is in turmoil. Currently the Republicans, following president Lincoln's lead, are in control, and willing to end the war by re-uniting the nation with military force. The Democrats, on the other hand, are more willing to enter in to negotiations with the Confederacy, which could eventually lead to a more peaceful solution. This needs to be taken into consideration during the future military campaigns, as currently Lincoln has the support of the majority of citizens within the Union. In case the Union military is unsuccessful, it is very likely that Lincoln's support will plummet. This effect will be seen no later than the House of Representatives elections in late 1862.\n\tWe also hear of news acrross the Atlantic, that the French and British are considering siding with the Confederacy to secure a steady flow of cotton!

-1
2
01-01-1900
The Bloodiest War in America!
Casualties Mounting!
Both Sides Gain Grand Victories!
Number of Volunteers Plummeting!
New Campaign Objectives!
A War so Terrible!
18
\tThe Civil War continues more terrible than ever. Even with the superiority in potential, the Union has not been able to quell the Southern rebellion. As the war drags on, exhaustion is setting in.\n\tIf the War is not to end soon, the next critical milestone in sight is the Union Presidential Election of 1864. If the Union military is not victorious, it's possible that the anti-Lincoln forces will gain such momentum, that a new President is elected, causing turmoil in Union policy making, and most likely forcing the Union to enter into negotiations with the Confederacy to end the War. This would lead to an end of hostilities and a Confederate victory!\n\tFor both sides it's imperative to maintain the armies fighting condition, and to inflict severe losses on the enemy, as the number of volunteers is diminishing and support for the war effort is starting to waver. 

