01-01-1900
Lincoln Re-Elected!
Peace-Democrats Losing Support!
War Exhaustion Setting In!
High Mortality Among the Wounded!
New Campaign Objectives!
Civil Wars leave nothing but tombs.
18
\tThe Civil War has raged on for more than three long years now. The amount of casualties is staggering, and the citizens on both sides are tired of the war, and tired of seeing their loved ones killed in battle.\n\tIn the Union, President Abraham Lincoln has secured a second term, winning the November elections. It's now clear that the Civil War will be fought to the bitter end, and a peaceful solution by negotiation is out of the question. The North will never recognize the Confederacy as a nation among nations, unless itself is militarily defeated and forced to sue for peace.\n\tIt's now up to the armies and their commanders to defeat their opponent in detail, and to inflict such high casualties that the citizens' will to resist is crushed. The Civil War is now a total war.

