01-01-1900
French Intervention!
Napoleon III to Support the Confederacy!
Expeditionary Army on the Move!
French Fleet enters the Coast of Texas!
The French Recognize the Confederacy!
Ironclad Normandie of the French Fleet.
13
\tAfter the French Expeditionary Corps, supported by the Confederate States, managed to deal a decisive blow against Mexican forces, the French are in full control of the country and Mexican Republican resistance is all but crushed. With Mexican auxilaries and other European volunteers supporting the French in maintaining public order, the main body of the Expeditionary Corps, under General Forey, is marching north with Admirals de La Graviere and Bouet supporting with the French Navy.\n\tEmperor Napoleon III has declared the French are supporting the Confederacy to rightfully defend themselves against the unjust northern aggression. The Confederacy is providing the French with bases and supplies, while Forey's vanguard from the corps of over 30,000 veterans, including the Foreign Legion, moves into Texas from the south.\n\tThe world watches in awe as the American Civil War escalates.
Mexico
