01-01-1900
The British are Coming!
British Army in Canada Mobilized!
Reinforcements Crossing the Atlantic!
Confederacy Recognized by the British!
Union Surrounded by Enemies!
British Intervention Force Mobilized.
16
\tAfter diplomatic relations deteriorated between the British Empire and the Union, the British have made a decision to no longer be by-standers in the American Civil War.\n\tIn Canada, the British forces and Canadian militia under Sir Fenwick Williams have been mobilized to defend the Province. While inexperienced and lacking manpower, the Army is still a considerable threat to the Union flank.\n\tIn London, British commander-in-chief the Duke of Cambridge has ordered the British Army to reinforce North America, placing Admiral Milne as overall commander of the operation. The British fleet that took part in the Mexican intervention has already sailed out, and Milne's main Force is expected within weeks, bringing with them highly experienced British veterans.\n\tThe British also recognize the Confederate States of America to be a sovereign nation, which boosts morale in the Confederacy, with people celebrating in the streets.
London, England
