01-01-1900
Spanish Intervention!
General Prim wants Revenge!
Confederacy Surrounded by Enemies!
French Providing a Passage through Mexico!
Celebration in the Union!
General Juan Prim of Spain.
17
\tFollowing the deterioration of relations between Europe and the Confederacy, there are now dramatic new events taking place in Mexico. Spain, who lost Cuba to American Filibusters in the early 1850s have been the loudest European opposers of the Confederate States. With this latest development, Spain is openly opposing the Confederacy and preparing military retaliations.\n\tGeneral Juan Prim's Intervention Force in Mexico has reportedly received orders from Madrid to divert from any further operations in Mexico and to prepare for an expedition further north. While small in size, the Spanish force could be used to raid the Confederate coast in the Gulf of Mexico, supported by the Spanish fleet under Casto Mendez Nunez.\n\tWhile not directly allying with the Union, people in the United States heartily welcome this intervention, as it is now certain there will not be further sympathy for the Confederate cause arriving from Europe.
Madrid, Spain
