01-01-1900
The French Beaten!
French Forces in Flight!
Union Morale Soars!
Napoleon III Backing Down!
Confederates Disappointed!
Napoleon III Skedaddles.
11
\tThe French have suffered staggering losses in fighting against the Union armies! What was supposed to be an elite European force to turn the tide in the American Civil War has been utterly humiliated and demoralized, forcing the great Emperor Napoleon III to abandon North America.\n\tWhile the news creates wild celebration in Union, the mood is much darker in the Confederacy, who have lost a strong ally in its fight towards lasting Independence. The retreating French have also shown arrogance towards their recent hosts. Public order has suffered where the French columns have been marching, with Southern Ladies spitting terrifying curses and insults at the former allies, and the French soldiers looting and foraging Confederate property.\n\tWith these latest events, Confederate citizens seem to be losing heart, as the overwhelming Union armies are triumphant.

