01-01-1900
The Spanish Beaten!
Prim's Force in Retreat!
Spanish Prestige Tarnished!
Confederate Military Victorious!

General Prim's Army has been defeated.
17
\tThe Spanish intervention in the American Civil War, which was supposed to give them the satisfaction of avenging the loss of Cuba in the 1850s, has turned into a humiliating retreat from North America. General Prim's Army and the supporting fleet have been dealt a decisive blow, and the forces are all but destroyed and scattered. It is believed that this defeat will end any Spanish ambitions anywhere near the Gulf of Mexico.\n\tThe Confederate victory is widely celebrated in Southern cities and the Confederate colonies of Cuba and Nicaragua, though the native citizens are nowhere to be seen in these celebrations.\n\tNow the Confederacy can fully focus on dealing with the Union, as the Spanish thorn in their side has been removed.

