06-03-1862
French Invasion!
General Lorencez Lands with his Troops!
More Troops on their Way?
Napoleon III to conquer Mexico?
French Fleets Blockading the Coast!
French Invasion of Mexico underway.
12
\tThe European intervention in Mexico is proceeding in accordance with the Convention of Soledad. So far we have seen the capture of Veracruz, and European forces advancing to Orizaba, Cordoba and Tehuacan. The city of Campeche surrendered to the French fleet on February 27.\n\tThe latest news is the arrival of French troops under General Charles Ferdinand Latrille, Comte de Lorencez, with reports indicating thousands of troops are under his command, which makes their commitment to follow the Convention questionable. Already we hear rumors of the British and Spanish questioning the French ambition in Mexico.\n\tSo far the intervention force has enjoyed success, but we hear reports of Mexican commander General Ignacio Zaragoza preparing an army to fight any further invasion attempts. What started as an intervention to settle Mexican dept, may escalate into large scale fighting! The Grand Herald will keep you informed of the latest events.
Mexico
