10-04-1862
Mexican Intervention Escalates!
The British and Spanish Withdraw!
Napoleon III Vows to Conquer Mexico!
The French Push Inland!
Mexican Army in Disarray!
French Emperor Napoleon III.
11
\tThe European intervention into Mexico is turning into an invasion! Reports indicate that the British and Spanish forces in Mexico are already withdrawing after realising the French are not there to only collect payments of debt, but to conquer the whole country.\n\tThe British fleet under commodore Hugh Dunlop has moved in to extract the small force of British troops, and Spanish General Juan Prim's force of some 7,000 men is also moving to embark. What remains is the French Expeditionary Corps, under General de Lorencez, which is preparing to move inland to capture Mexico City.\n\tThe French ambition to conquer Mexico would also open a line of supply to the Confederacy. It is said that Emperor Napoleon III wishes to open a trade route to Texas in order to control the European cotton trade. Any other support for the Confederacy remains questionable, but if the French plan succeeds, we could see a French controlled Mexico as a neighbour to the Confederacy within months!
Mexico
