13-12-1862
Xalapa Fallen!
The French Invasion Continues!
French Reinforcements Arrive!
General Bazaine Marches On!
Mexican Forces in Retreat!
French Emperor Napoleon III.
14
\tFor a moment it looked like the French invasion of Mexico had come to an end after the humiliating defeat in the Battle of Puebla. But instead, the French managed to contain the pursuing Mexicans at Orizaba, Veracruz, on June 14.\n\tAfter the situation was stabilized, the French shipped in substantial reinforcements. More troops have been arriving since September, with General Bazaine and the main body of the reinforcements landing in October. Bazaine's renewed offensive has already captured the port of Tampico and the latest city to fall was Xalapa, Veracruz, where the Mexicans offered no resistance.\n\tThe French now have a considerable force in Mexico, with a strong fleet and the elite Foreign Legion also deployed. It seems a matter of time before we hear about further French advances into the Mexico interior. 
Mexico
