16-06-1863
Mexico City Fallen!
General Forey Victorious!
Mexican Forces in Retreat!
Legionnaires Pave the Way to Victory!
Trade to Mexico only via the French!
Second Battle of Puebla a French Victory.
14
\tSince our last report, the French offensive in Mexico has gained momentum. On June 7, French troops under General Bazaine entered Mexico City itself. Since then, after the arrival of the main army under General Forey, the French have been quick to set up a puppet administration lead by General Almonte.\n\tOn the march to Mexico City the French fought multiple battles, most notable being the Battle of Camaron on April 30, where a patrol of 62 Foreign Legionnaires fought of a force of 3,000 Mexicans; only three Legionnaires survived! On May 17 the French got their retribution as the besieged city of Puebla surrendered, after General Bazaine defeated the Mexican army under General Comonfort, forcing President Juarez to flee into exile with the state treasury.\n\tWith Mexico under Napoleon III's control, all trade to Mexico is now controlled by the French.
Mexico
