17-06-1863
French Intervention Possible!
Napoleon III Thanks The Confederacy!
French Reinforcements On the Way!
Ironclad Normandie Sighted!
Hopes High In the Confederacy!
The French Ironclad Normandie.
13
\tThe French Emperor Napoleon III has publicly offered thanks to the Confederate States of America, for their military assistance in the conquest of Mexico. He says it was thanks to the mainly Texan troops sent to help them, that the Mexican Republican army was forced to split and encounter another invasion from the north, allowing the French to defeat the main body in detail.\n\tWith the Mexican army utterly defeated, the French have managed to take control of most of the country. Since the fall of Mexico City, more reinforcements have arrived, bolstering the French force in Mexico to more than 40,000 strong, including some 3,000 men from the elite Foreign Legion and African Light Infantry Battalions. The Intervention Fleet is also considerable, with the ironclad Normandie as the flagship.\n\tThe French are re-deploying their force at this moment, with the Mexican auxilaries and foreign Voluntary troops, mainly Belgian and Austrian, taking responsibility to maintain civil order in the countryside.
Mexico
