01-06-1864
Maximilian Emperor of Mexico!
Mexico a Catholic Monarchy!
Treaty of Miramar Signed!
French in Full control!
Abolition of Child Labor!
French Emperor Napoleon III.
11
\tAfter the French occupied Mexico City, French Emperor Napoleon III has taken steps to create a puppet government in Mexico. To consolidate his control of Mexico, Maximilian I was pressured by Napoleon III to accept the Mexican crown, which he did on October 3, 1863. Maximilian I, the younger brother of Austrian Emperor Franz Joseph I had a glorious career in the Austrian navy before moving to Mexico.\n\tMaximilain formally accepted the crown on April 10, signing the Treaty of Miramar, and was subsequently enthroned as Emperor of Mexico alongside his wife Carlota of Belgium. Under Maximilian's rule the country is a limited monarchy with a democratically elected congress.\n\tSo far, under Maximilian's rule, laws to abolish child labor, limit working hours and abolish the system of land tenancy have been passed. This has won him little support among the Mexican conservatives, foreshadowing difficult times for him as the Emperor.
Mexico
