14-05-1861
British Declare Neutrality!
Royal Navy to Avoid American Ports!
Any blockades to be monitored by Adm. Milne!
The Admiralty to Reinforce Milne!
4,300 Regular British Troops in Canada!
Royal Navy is observing the Civil War.
16
\tThe British Empire has issued a Proclamation of Neutrality regarding the American Civil War, this follows Rear Admiral Sir Alexander Milne's orders from last December to avoid any measure of demonstration likely to give umbrage to either party in the United States. Since then the Royal Navy has avoided the American Coast.\n\tMilne, in command of the North America and West Indies station of the Royal Navy has received reinforcements as the British Admiralty is concerned about her neutral rights. British warships of Milne's station have been ordered to protect commerce against any intrusions from either side.\n\tReports state that in Canada the British regular forces number no more than 5,000 men after the majority of troops left to fight in Crimea in 1854-55. The Commander in Chief in North America, General Sir William Fenwick Williams has been requesting reinforcements regularly since the Civil War broke out.
London, England
