24-12-1860
Secession!
South Carolina Leaves the Union!
Governor Pickens in Charge!
U.S. Property Confiscated!
Union Falling Apart!
Secession Convention held in South Carolina.
26
\tDisunion! Disaster! The United States has broken apart, with the state of South Carolina seceding officially on December 20, 1860. to-day, we are given the Declaration of the Immediate Causes which Induce and Justify the Secession.\n\t"And increasing hostility on the part of the non-slaveholding States to the institution of slavery, has led to a disregard of their obligations, and the laws of the General Government have ceased to effect the objects of the Constitution" the Declaration states. The state is now run by Governor Francis W. Pickens, who himself was not among the signatories for the ordinance of secession, even though strongly advocating secession of Southern states. Reports have it, that in South Carolina local militias are being mustered and mobilized, with state officials approving confiscation of U.S. property.\n\tThe U.S. Army garrison in Charleston Harbor, under the command of Major Robert Anderson, has withdrawn to the safety of Forts Moultrie and Sumter to await orders from the Buchanan Administration.\n\tThe situation is alarming, and could escalate easily!
Charleston, SC
