23
09-01-1861
Guns Fired at U.S. Ship!
Star of the West Under Attack!
Maj. Anderson Prepares to Retaliate!
Supplies to Fort Sumter Stopped!
General Engagement Avoided!
Fort Sumter in Charleston Harbor, SC.
22
\tRebel guns have fired at the U.S. Navy ship Star of the West! The ship was carrying supplies for the surrounded U.S. Garrison under Maj. Robert Anderson, holding Fort Sumter in Charleston Harbor. The fire was directed by cadets from The Citadel, stationed on Morris Island, and Fort Moultrie's batteries joined in, forcing the ship to turn back.\n\tStar of the West is an unarmed civilian merchant ship, as derelict ships sunk as obstacles prevented USS Brooklyn, a Sloop-of-War, entering the harbor earlier. President Buchanan, dismayed at Anderson's move to Sumter, ordered the relief expedition, which has now failed.\n\tCharleston Harbor is not a Hornet's Nest, with the South Carolina militia having seized all U.S. defensive positions and the arsenal, including 20,000 weapons. Large numbers of rebel guns point at Sumter and the inlet, preventing any U.S. movement, and the defenses are being reinforced with a floating battery.\n\tTo-day escalation was prevented by Maj. Anderson, who chose not to retaliate and start a general engagement. Tensions rise, with the future of the nation on hold.
Charleston, SC
