24
10-01-1861
Mississippi Secedes!
Florida Secedes!
Union Falling Apart!
Presd't. Buchanan Powerless!
New State Militias Formed!
Mississippi State House in Jackson.
28
\tMore Seceding States! After the Secession of South Carolina in December, further Southern states have held secession conventions, declaring secession from the Union.\n\tMississippi voted in favor of secession by a vote of 83-15 with one absentia, becoming the second state to secede yesterday. In Jackson the result was received with the most vociferous cheering and Oxfrord brilliantly illuminated. Bells are ringing and guns fired with the gallant State receiving cheers. "Our position is thoroughly identified with the institution of slavery - the greatest material interest of the world" the Mississippi Secession Convention declared, continuing "we resolve to maintain our rights with the full consciousness of the justice of the course, and the undoubting belief of our ability to maintain it."\n\tOnly a day later, to-day, the State of Florida officially seceded from the Union, simply declaring its severing of ties with the Federal Union, without stating any causes. The secession was is met with celebrations in Tampa. Florida officials received telegrams from Mississippi and Georgia, affirming support for Floridas action.

