11-01-1861
Alabama Secedes!
Delegates from all Slave States meet in Montgomery!
Lincoln's Election the Last Straw!
Quearrel over Slavery!
Further Secession Imminent!
Delegates from all Slave states meet in Montgomery.
26
\tThe secession criris deepens, with Alabama following the example of South Carolina, Mississippi and Florida. The Alabama Secession Convention also invited delegates from all other 14 slaveholding states to meet at Montgomery. Sources say preparations are being made to form a slaveholding Southern Republic from the seceded states. More states are preparing to secede, and it's only a matter of who will go next. Will it be Louisiana or Georgia?\n\tThe reasoning for Alabama's decision can be seen in a letter from Stephen F. Hale to the Governor of Kentucly in December. In it he states the election of Lincoln is a "solemn decleration... of hostility to the South, her property and institutions-nothing less than an open declaration of war..." Hale stated fears of destruction and horror in the case that the African race would be allowed to roam free in the South.\n\tA new Constitution is beign drafted, forbidding the emancipation of slaves in the State by the State itself or any other country. It also strongly opposes the African slave trade.
Montgomery, AL
