Louisiana Secedes!
Ordinance of Secession Adopted!
A Night Parade in New Orleans!
Cannons firing in Louisiana!
Louisiana Called a Country!
The Convention voted 113 to 17 to adopt Ordinance of Secession.
26
\tLouisiana becomes the sixth State to secede! The Ordinance of Secession declares to "dissolve the union between the State of Louisiana and other States united with her under the compact entitled The Constitution of the United States of America."\n\tLouisiana has opposed the election of Abraham Lincoln, one newspaper saying the Republican Party opposed the dignity, interest and well-being of Louisiana. Mr. Lincoln has been called a black Republican Abolitionist who would end the way of life in Louisiana.\n\tAfter the Secession Convention voted, 113 in favor and 17 against secession, the people have taken to the streets, with parades, fireworks and cannon fire in New Orleans.
Baton Rouge, LA
