Texas Secedes!
Ordinance of Secession Adopted!
166 to 8 Vote!
Seventy Yeas Before a Single Nay!
A Referendum to Follow!
Texas Became the Seventh State to Secede.
26
\tThe Texas Secession Convention has adopted an Ordinance of Secession by a vote of 166 vs. a mere 8, becoming the seventh state to cut ties with the Federal Union. Texas Governor Sam Houston urged the State, in vain, to reject secession. Instead, he was removed from the governorship and replaced by his Lieutenant Edward Clark. The next step for Texas is a referendum, which will unquestionably vote for the secession.\n\tThe Texas Convention is drafting a document called the Declaration of the Causes which Impel the State of Texas to Secede from the Federal Union. The Declaration lists reasons for the secession, including solidarity with its sister slave-holding states, the U.S. Government's inability to prevent Indian attacks, slave-stealing raids and cross-border banditry, and outrages committed by northern politicians and abolitionists upon Texas.\n\t"We hold as undeniable truths that the governments of the various States, and of the confederacy itself, were established exclusively by the white race, for themselves and their posterity; that the African race had no agency in their establishment", says the Declaration.
Texas
