A Convention in Montgomery!
Confederacy Established!
Constitution Drafted!
Gen'l. Twiggs Surrenders in Texas!
Davis to Become the President!
A Convention in Montgomery, AL, established the Confederacy.
26
\tOn February 4, conventions from secession States sent representatives to meet at the Montgomery Convention. There fundamental documents of government were promulgated and a provisional government established. The seven States now form the Confederate States of America, and the drafting of a constitution is underway.\n\tNews from Texas has arrived, with information that the Commissioners of Public Safety have negotiated with the Federal Government for the safe transfer of military installations and bases in Texas to the Confederates. U.S. Army General Twiggs has surrendered federal property in San Antonia, including military stores. Twiggs delivered his entire Army property, including 10,000 rifled muskets to the Confederacy, which has been called an act of treason by the Unionists in Texas and elsewhere. President Buchanan has ordered General Twiggs to be dismissed from the U.S. Army for treachery to the flag of his country.\n\tU.S. Army Colonel Robert E. Lee, in San Antonia at the time, upon hearing of Twiggs' surrender, is noted having said "Has it come so soon as this?"
Montgomery, AL
