04-03-1861
Lincoln Inaugurated!
The 16th President of the U.S!
A New Cabinet to Handle Crisis!
Buchanan Leaves Office.
Northern Population Calls for Action!
Inauguration of President Abraham Lincoln.
25
\tHail to the Chief! Abraham Lincoln is inaugurated the 16th President of the United States to-day. His controversial election is said to have triggered the current secession crisis at hand, and now it is him, after the lame duck Buchanan has stepped down, who needs to steer the Ship of the Union in this crisis.\n\tLincoln and his "radical Republicans" were feared to abolish slavery in the United States despite the opposition of the southern states. The election of Lincoln is what triggered the secession in the first place. Now the crisis will most likely escalate further, as the Lincoln administration is already getting ready to call the militia of the provisional army. This militia call would surely trigger other southern states to secede, and to spiral the situation out of hand and in to a Civil War.\n\tBut Lincoln must act, as the population and his supporters are calling for action against the southern rebels, who have seized U.S. property and weapons. Any delay in doing so will lower his support in the north. It seems the War is inevitable!
Washington, D.C.
