05-03-1861
Virginia's Loyalty to Union Questioned!
Rumors of Increasing Support for Secession!
Further States Threatening to Leave the Union!
Confederate Support in Virginia Soars!
Virginia is the Powerhouse of the South!
Could We See C.S. Capital in Virginia?
35
\tVirginia, the Old Dominion State, is strategically the most important southern slave state. It's the industrial center of the South, with its output nearly equal to that of all the Confederate states combined. It is also home to one of the most advanced shipyards in North America, Gosport.\n\tThe importance of Virginia has not escaped either side of the secession crisis. After Virginia's initial vote not to secede, the Union leadership has done everything in its power to make sure the Virginians will remain in the Union.\n\tRecent events have seen Confederate support increase in Virginia, and it is most likely that in the case of an armed confrontation Virginia could declare neutrality or even secede. So far the Confederate leaders have had difficulty in securing other slave states bordering the free states of the Union. Recent reports from Montgomery, Alabama, indicate, that in the case that Virginia seceded, to consolidate the Confederate hold of the state, Richmond would be made the capital city of the Confederate States. This would put the capitals of the Union and the C.S.A. only some one hundred miles apart!

