38th U.S. Congress to be Chosen!
Democratic Support Rising!
Lincoln Needs a Victory!
Oregon Votes Republican!
Abe Lincoln's Last Card; Or, Rouge-et-Noir.
36
\tThe 1862 United States elections are held in the midst of a Civil War! Members of the 38th United States Congress are chosen in this election. The elections started to-day, and the Oregon votes are in. The single seat from Oregon will change from Democratic to Republican!\n\tThe elections will continue until November 1863, but the majority of seats will be decided during and before the Election Day, November 4, 1862. What is certain already, is that there will be vacancies as many seceded states are unrepresented.\nIn previous elections the Republicans won 108 seats while the Democratic Party won only 45. This time the Democratic support is already much higher, with many in the party opposing Lincoln's leadership in the crisis. Samuel Sullican "Sunset" Cox, leader of the Democratic party, is expecting a land-slide victory.\n\tIn the Confederacy the people are hoping for Democratic victory, as this would undermine Lincoln's ability to fight the war, and probably result in peace negotiations with the South!

