National Unity Party Formed!
War Democrats Join Lincoln!
Republican Party Diverging!
Elections on November 8, 1864!
National Union Party Ticket, 1864.
38
\tThe Republican Party is in turmoil! Senators Charles Sumner and Henry Wilson from Massachusetts want the Party to advocate racial equality before the law. Not all northern Republicans support such measures. Lately a group of Republican dissidents, who call themselves Radical Republicans, formed their own party. It was feared that Lincoln would not get sufficient support in the coming 1864 elections.\n\tBut now some War Democrats have joined the Republicans to form a National Unity Party. This new party has nominated Lincoln for a second term at the convention on June 7-8.\n\tThe party's platform includes goals such as the pursuit of the war and the unconditional surrender of the Confederacy, the abolition of slavery, aid to disabled Union veterans, continued European neutrality, the enforcement of the Monroe Doctrine, the encouragement of immigration, and the construction of a transcontinental railroad. In short, if Lincoln is re-elected, the war will be fought to the bitter end, with no peace talks with the Confederacy.

