\tThe Democratic Party is split between War Democrats and Peace Democrats. The latter are split between the Moderate Peace Democrats and the Copperheads, who declare that the war is a failure and favor an immediate end of hostilities without securing Union victory.\n\tWith the party in disarray, and the War Democrats having formed the National Unity Party with Republicans to support Lincoln's second term, the convention of 29th August has chosen one of Lincoln's generals, a pro-war candidate, to run, with anti-war Representative George Hunt Pendleton. Pendleton's choice will balance the ticket to appeal to both pro-war and anti-war Democrat voters.\n\tThe race for the presidency is predicted to become narrow between the two candidates, with the fortunes of war deciding the outcome. If the Union armies are victorius, it's most likely Lincoln will be re-elected. But with each military failure the opposition will become stronger, and it's also a well known fact in the Confederacy!

