\tIt's a day of national disaster in the Union! Yesterday, on April 14, 10:14 p.m. the 16th President of the United States was mortally shot in the head at Ford's Theatre by the assassin John Wilkes Booth. The President passed away this morning at 07:22 a.m.\n\tIWitness accounts state that Booth entered the back of Lincoln's theater box, crept up from behind and fired the shot. Lincoln's guest, a major, momentarily grappled with Booth, but was stabbed and Booth managed to escape. Lincoln died after eight hours in a coma. Booth is on the run with the U.S. military tracking him down.\n\tIt's now up to Vice-President Andrew Johnson to take the lead. Rumors have it that Johnson too was a target for assasination, but the would-be perpetrator got scared and did not carry out his plans. Johnson, after visiting the dying Lincoln, said: "They shall suffer for this." Johnson's demeanor can be described as solemn and dignified, but some Cabinet members speak of him being drunk at the inauguration. In these circumstances sober and clear-headed discretion is required.

