39
\tPresident Lincoln's assassin, John Wilkes Booth has met his end. Surrounded by Federal troops, he refused to surrender and was gunned down by Sergeant Boston Corbett. It's still under investigation whether Booth was about to fire at the soldiers, or if Corbett simply shot him without order, pretext or excuse, and against the order to take him alive.\n\tThe murder of an American President has been condemned even by Confederate Generals. One of the high ranking officers called the murder "a discrace of the age", while others too have expressed regret at Lincoln's death by Booth's hand. Booth's body has been taken by a U.S. Navy ironclad to Washington Navy Yard for identification and an autopsy.\n\tBooth had written a letter which was seized by Federal troops. In this letter Booth explains he has "ever held the South was right", justifying secession.

