\tTexas has proclaimed its secession from the Union and has been admitted to the Confederate States, withdrawing from Congress. This officially makes Texas the seventh state in the Confederacy. As the Union dissolves, Americans are holding their breath. Shall more states secede?\n\tIn other news, the Union has reorganized its territories in the West. The Dakota Territory has been organized from the Nebraska Territory and the unorganized territory north of it. The Nebraska Territory's western border has been moved to 27 degrees west of Washington, gaining small portions of the Utah and Washington Territories. The Nevada Territory was organized from the Utah Territory west of 39 degrees from Washington. Also the Colorado Territory was officially organized by Act of Congress on February 28, 1861.\n\tIt's the cartographers who are now working exceptionally hard, as the maps change so often, that new ones are needed before the old orders have been delivered to all those who need them. And it's still unclear, whether the two sides in this crisis can agree on these borders.

