Morrill Land-Grant Act Signed!
Lincoln Signs the Act into Law!
Engineering Education Boosted!
Government to Donate Public Lands!
U.S. to Lead Technical Studies!
Modern Engineering Feats in the U.S.
42
\tTo-day, the President of the United States, Abraham Lincoln, has signed the Morrill Land-Grant Act into Law. The Act passed the Senate on June 10 and the House on June 17.\n\tThe Land-Grant Agricultural and Mechanical College Act donates Public Lands to several States and Territories which may then provide Colleges for the Benefit of Agriculture and the Mechanic Arts. The land grant colleges are to transform engineering education in America and boost the United States into the position of world leader in technical education.\n\tCurrently American colleges train students in classical studies and the liberal arts. Education is for the affluent and entrance requirements often require proficiency in the dead languages of Latin and Greek, excluding all the working classes. American engineers are mostly educated at the United States Military Academy, on fortress construction, and their instructors are the authors of most engineering texts of to-day. The Morrill Act plans to change all of that.

