Killings After Surrender!
U.S. Commanders Furious!
Confederates Refusing Exchange!
Lincoln to Retaliate!
Confederates Massacring Colored Troops.
46
\tWhen the United States adopted the policy of recruiting and training black volunteers to the form United States Colored Troops regiments, it caused great uproar in the Southern Confederacy. Any captured soldiers of color have not received the treatment of their white counterparts. During recent fighting, a large number of colored troops were mercilessly massacred after surrendering.\n\tBefore this bleak, sad event, President Lincoln had already written an Order of Retaliation to prevent such treatment. The Order says, "It is therefore ordered that for every soldier of the United States killed in violation of the laws of war, a rebel soldier shall be executed; and for every one enslaved by the enemy or sold into slavery a rebel soldier shall be placed at hard labor on the public works, and continued at such labor until the other shall be released and receive the treatment due to a prisoner of war." It remains to be seen whether the threat is enough to prevent similar blood-letting in the future.

