\tThe U.S. army has been planning to withdraw many of its units from the Great Plains to fight in the Civil War. But before the withdrawal could begin, a commander of the Colorado Volunteers has reported that indians had stolen 175 head of cattle from whites. The Cheyenne indians stated the cattle was wanderďng freely on the plains. During the following days, there has been a number of confrontations between the indians and the militia men, with the loss of life and the burning of Cheyenne Tipis.\n\tThe indians are reportedly puzzled by what they regard as unprovoked attacks by soldiers. There are even speculations that the Colorado Volunteers are trying to avoid being ordered to go to Kansas by establishing a need for them to remain in Colorado.\n\tWhatever the truth, fighting is reportedly escalating between the militiamen and the Dog Soldiers.

