\tA high ranking general in the Union Army has issued General Order No. 11, ordering Jews to be expelled from his military district. This controversial order has already caused a loud outcry in the political leadership and the press.\n\tThe Jewish population in the U.S. is estimated to be between 150,000 and 200,000, a dramatic increase from a mere 15,000 in 1840. Many emigrated from Europe as the U.S. promised economic and social freedom, which they did not enjoy in Europe.\n\tEven if anti-Semitism is wide in the South, as well as in the North, the Jews are seen as secessionists and rebels, destroying the national credit. The interviewed military officials are claiming that the Jews are behind the black market of cotton smuggling to the North, which damages the Union's ability to squeeze the South economically. With General Order No. 11, many Jewish families have been expelled, even violently, by the Union Army.

