\tTensions in Missouri are running high, as the state seems to be drifting towards secession. The state had entered the Union as a slave state following the Missouri Compromise of 1820, which was nullified in 1854 by permitting the Kansas and Nebraska Territories to vote on slavery. This resulted in bitter fighting, "Bleeding Kansas". In the recent presidential elections Lincoln received only 10% of Missouri's votes, indicating their the state's stance towards his ideals.\n\tNews from the state indicate Governor Claiborne Jackson, a known Southern sympathizer, has sought to use the state militia to his advantage. On February 13, Gen'l. Frost formed Missouri Volunteer Militia companies composed entirely of pro-secessionist "Minutemen", which could be used to advance on to St.Louis, and the U.S. armory there, if needed. To counter this sentiment, an Unconditional Union Party was formed to support the preservation of the Union at all costs. It seems very likely that the stance of armed neutrality will not succeed for long.
