01-01-1900
A Recruitment Crisis!
The Union Unable to Fill the Ranks!
The Congress in an Emergency Meeting!
New Laws Being Drafted!
Forcecd Recruitment Feared!
Union Recruitment in Crisis.
65
\tThe Union is facing unprecedented difficulties in filling the ranks of their armies. Whether it's the terms of service, or the recruitment quotas, the number of available recruits has dropped so low, that forming new regimnets has all but ceased around the nation.\n\tThe President and the Congress have started drafting and implementing new recruitment laws in all haste to enable further expansion of the military. It will take some time to pass the required laws, and it's widely feared that the Union is vulnerable to attacks during this period.\n\tCitizens around the nation are worried that the new measures will enable the government further control over their lives, including forced service in the military, and already there's unrest and protests in many major cities, including sporadic riots that have been forcibly subdued by the local militias.

